        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "In the reference guide, chapter 12.5. \"The Standard Router\", there are rewrite configurations for Apache HTTP Server, Lighttpd and IIS. I think there should also be an example for rewrite rules for the Nginx web server. I have already written such a configuration and it works well on my server.\n\n\n{code}\nif (!-e $request_filename) {\n  rewrite ^.*$ \/index.php last;\n}\n{code}\n\nI translated it from the extended Apache mod_rewrite example, I'm quite sure it works the same."
        },
